FOR MR. PANTS?

00:51.384 --> 00:52.677
[laughs]

00:55.388 --> 00:59.058
YOUR LOSS.

01:02.145 --> 01:03.313
- OH, PLEASE, HAPPY.

01:03.396 --> 01:04.605
YOU TAKE IT.

01:04.688 --> 01:06.274
I KNOW YOU LOVE
NOVELTY COOKIE JARS.

01:06.357 --> 01:07.650
- I'LL TAKE IT.

01:07.734 --> 01:08.902
I KNOW SOME SQUIRRELS

01:08.985 --> 01:10.737
WHO WILL THINK
THIS IS HILARIOUS.

01:10.820 --> 01:12.739
squeak!

01:26.628 --> 01:28.505
[farting]

01:29.756 --> 01:30.840
[sizzling]

01:30.924 --> 01:32.050
[stammering]
H-HOT PEPPER!

01:32.133 --> 01:33.593
H-HOT PEPPER!
H-HOT PEPPER!

01:33.676 --> 01:35.512
HOT PEPPER!
HOT PEPPER!

01:35.595 --> 01:38.473
- AH, THE TRICK
IS TO NOT TASTE THE HOT PART.

01:38.556 --> 01:39.808
[chuckles]

01:39.891 --> 01:41.434
HAVE SOME H2O, BRO.

01:41.518 --> 01:42.519
- [squealing]

01:42.602 --> 01:45.021
- NO, AFTER YOU.

01:45.104 --> 01:46.815
YES, YES, YES,
MY TONGUE IS DYING,

01:46.898 --> 01:48.650
BUT I INSIST YOU GO AHEAD.

01:48.733 --> 01:50.276
- [gulping]

01:50.360 --> 01:50.860
[sighs]

01:50.944 --> 01:53.071
- [gulping]
AH...

01:53.154 --> 01:53.738
poof!

01:53.822 --> 01:56.699
HAPPY, LOOK AT YOUR HAIR.

01:56.783 --> 01:58.993
[laughs]

01:59.077 --> 02:00.411
YOU LOOK LIKE AN EXPENSIVE MOP.

02:00.495 --> 02:02.539
poof!

02:02.622 --> 02:03.665
[gasps]

02:03.748 --> 02:06.459
- [laughing]

02:06.543 --> 02:07.961
- WHAT?

02:08.044 --> 02:12.298
"HAIRY GARCIA"?

02:12.382 --> 02:14.926
- HEY, THAT'S MY HAIR POTION.

02:15.009 --> 02:15.844
YOU'RE NOT SUPPOSED
TO DRINK THAT.

02:15.927 --> 02:18.555
THAT GOES ON MY HEAD.

02:18.638 --> 02:20.265
- HAIR POTION?

02:20.348 --> 02:23.434
- HOW DO YOU THINK I GOT
THESE LONG, LUSCIOUS LOCKS?

02:23.518 --> 02:26.855
- THIS IS...
AWESOME!

02:26.938 --> 02:30.066
[camera shutter snaps]

02:30.149 --> 02:32.026
LOOK, YOU CAN DO THIS...

02:32.110 --> 02:34.404
OR THIS...

02:34.487 --> 02:35.572
OR THIS...

02:35.655 --> 02:37.240
[applause]

02:37.323 --> 02:39.826
OR THIS.

02:39.909 --> 02:42.412
WHOO! WHAT A DAY
WE'RE GONNA HAVE WITH THIS HAIR.

02:42.495 --> 02:43.496
OH, THIS IS SO MUCH FUN.
WHAT COULD GO WRONG?

02:43.580 --> 02:47.333
[wind whistling]

02:50.336 --> 02:51.546
OOH...

02:51.629 --> 02:53.256
TIME TO GET A HAIRCUT.

02:56.593 --> 02:57.760
TWO NEAT 'N' TRIMS, PLEASE.

02:57.844 --> 03:01.598
[scissors clanging]

03:03.600 --> 03:05.894
THANK YOU, MY GOOD MAN.

03:07.854 --> 03:08.813
poof!

03:08.897 --> 03:09.856
poof!

03:14.777 --> 03:15.778
HERE.

03:15.862 --> 03:16.446
USE THE GOOD SCISSORS.

03:16.529 --> 03:18.573
WINK.

03:21.868 --> 03:25.622
[scissors clanging]

03:28.082 --> 03:29.042
poof!

03:32.795 --> 03:34.839
THAT THERE IS A 1978
LIMITED EDITION

03:34.923 --> 03:37.800
SACAGAWEA GOLD DOLLAR.

03:37.884 --> 03:40.929
SO HOW'S ABOUT A COUPLE OF CUTS
THAT STICK?

03:42.847 --> 03:45.975
[razor buzzing]

03:46.059 --> 03:47.018
poof!

03:48.186 --> 03:48.478
poof!

03:48.561 --> 03:49.479
poof!

03:49.562 --> 03:50.480
poof!

03:50.563 --> 03:52.440
[groaning]

03:54.901 --> 03:55.860
poof!

03:55.944 --> 03:57.820
ALL RIGHT, BUB.

03:57.904 --> 03:59.280
I DON'T KNOW
WHAT KIND OF SHAM OPERATION

03:59.364 --> 04:00.657
YOU'RE RUNNING HERE.

04:00.740 --> 04:04.661
DO I HAVE TO NAME-DROP
THE BETTER BUSINESS BUREAU?

04:04.744 --> 04:06.621
[weed whacker chugging]

04:06.704 --> 04:07.664
zzzzzt!

04:07.747 --> 04:09.666
THANK YOU.

04:09.749 --> 04:11.709
[bells jingle]

04:12.710 --> 04:14.921
poof!

04:15.004 --> 04:16.130
UGH!

04:16.214 --> 04:16.839
IT WON'T GO AWAY!

04:16.923 --> 04:19.425
HAPPY, WE NEED HELP.

04:19.509 --> 04:20.802
- COME ON, MAN,

04:20.885 --> 04:23.721
THIS DRUM WAS HAND MADE
OUT OF A BIGGER DRUM.

04:23.805 --> 04:26.391
HELP! THE HAIR,
IT JUST KEEPS GROWING,

04:26.474 --> 04:27.976
NO MATTER HOW MANY TIMES
WE CUT IT.

04:28.059 --> 04:29.269
YOU HAVE TO FIX IT.

04:29.352 --> 04:31.145
- BUT YOU GUYS LOOK AMAZING.

04:31.229 --> 04:33.815
SOMETIMES YOU GOT TO LET
THE FREAK FLAG FLY FREE.

04:33.898 --> 04:35.650
- FIX IT!
FIX IT!

04:35.733 --> 04:37.193
- OKAY, OKAY...

04:37.276 --> 04:38.695
LET'S SEE HERE.

04:38.778 --> 04:40.446
- UGH, LET ME AT IT.

04:40.530 --> 04:43.366
WE NEED A CURE!

04:43.449 --> 04:43.866
- WHOA.

04:43.950 --> 04:45.535
[faint squealing]

04:45.618 --> 04:48.579
- EH.

04:48.663 --> 04:49.706
crash!

04:49.789 --> 04:51.165
- [sniffing]

04:51.249 --> 04:53.710
AH...

04:53.793 --> 04:55.294
[whistling]

04:55.378 --> 04:58.339
- "DECLARATION OF CIVIL WAR."
NOT INTERESTED.

04:58.423 --> 04:59.882
- HEY!

04:59.966 --> 05:02.969
- HEY, MAN, SPLIT THAT
WITH YOU?

05:10.143 --> 05:13.187
[canned laughter from TV]

05:16.315 --> 05:17.275
- THERE'S NOTHING HERE.

05:17.358 --> 05:20.361
DON'T YOU HAVE ANYTHING
THAT CAN FIX US?

05:20.445 --> 05:23.197
- OH, UM...

05:23.281 --> 05:24.699
[twinkling]

05:24.782 --> 05:27.952
WAIT, I FORGOT
ABOUT THIS MAGIC JELLY BEAN.

05:28.036 --> 05:29.662
IT'LL FIX YOU RIGHT UP.

05:29.746 --> 05:31.289
IT'S GOOD FOR HICCUPS TOO.

05:32.957 --> 05:34.208
- [growls in protest]

05:34.292 --> 05:35.626
- OH, UH...

05:35.710 --> 05:38.296
YOU GOT TWO OF THESE, RIGHT?

05:38.379 --> 05:40.089
- I GOT TWO EARS.

05:40.173 --> 05:42.133
UH, SORRY, DUDES.

05:42.216 --> 05:45.595
THIS EAR'S
WHERE I KEEP MY BRAZIL NUT.

05:45.678 --> 05:46.929
[chomping]

05:52.810 --> 05:54.937
- I KNOW.

05:55.021 --> 05:56.564
WE'LL PLAY ROCK, PAPER, SCISSORS
FOR IT.

05:56.647 --> 05:57.398
- [barks]
ALL RIGHT.

05:57.482 --> 05:59.984
- ROCK, PAPER, SCISSORS!

06:00.068 --> 06:01.444
- [barks]
I WIN!

06:01.527 --> 06:02.236
- WHAT DO YOU MEAN,
YOU WIN?

06:02.320 --> 06:04.739
I CAN'T EVEN TELL
WHAT YOU PLAYED.

06:04.822 --> 06:05.990
- [barking argumentatively]

06:06.074 --> 06:08.201
- I DO NOT
ALWAYS PLAY SCISSORS.

06:08.284 --> 06:09.452
DO OVER.

06:09.535 --> 06:10.620
ROCK, PAPER, SCISSORS.

06:10.703 --> 06:11.788
SEE?

06:11.871 --> 06:12.955
- [barking victoriously]

06:13.039 --> 06:14.624
- WHAT?
NO WAY!

06:14.707 --> 06:16.459
IT COULD BE ANYTHING
UNDER THAT FUR.

06:16.542 --> 06:17.835
- [growls]

06:17.919 --> 06:19.879
- YOU DID NOT USE MIND TRICKS
TO GET ME TO PLAY "PAPER"

06:19.962 --> 06:21.130
BY SAYING
I ALWAYS PLAY SCISSORS--

06:21.214 --> 06:23.424
THIS ISN'T WORKING!

06:23.508 --> 06:25.676
CALL IT.

06:25.760 --> 06:28.304
- [barks]
HEADS!

06:28.387 --> 06:29.931
[barks victoriously]

06:30.014 --> 06:31.349
- NOT SO FAST, HAPPY.

06:31.432 --> 06:33.351
INTERNATIONAL COIN FLIP RULES
CLEARLY STATE

06:33.434 --> 06:36.521
THAT ONE MUST CATCH THE COIN
IN ONE HAND

06:36.604 --> 06:38.773
AND THEN FLIP IT ONTO
THE TOP OF THE OPPOSITE HAND,

06:38.856 --> 06:41.317
WHICH WOULD MAKE ME
THE WINNER.

06:41.400 --> 06:42.735
- [barking argumentatively]

06:42.819 --> 06:43.194
- WHAT, CHICAGO-STYLE RULES?

06:43.277 --> 06:45.029
THIS ISN'T 1953.

06:45.113 --> 06:48.199
- [barking argumentatively]

06:55.623 --> 06:55.915
- [gasps]

06:55.998 --> 06:58.251
[inhales]

06:58.334 --> 06:59.168
thunk!
UGH!

07:00.294 --> 07:03.005
[both yelling]

07:03.089 --> 07:06.175
[suspenseful music]

07:06.259 --> 07:10.346
♪ ♪

07:10.429 --> 07:12.849
[both gasp]

07:12.932 --> 07:14.183
[both sigh in relief]

07:14.267 --> 07:17.186
- THAT WAS WAY TOO CLOSE,
HAPS.

07:17.270 --> 07:20.356
TIME TO TAKE SECURITY MEASURES.

07:20.439 --> 07:24.360
BEN, UNTIL HAPPY AND I CAN REACH
A SATISFACTORY AGREEMENT,

07:24.443 --> 07:25.486
YOU HAVE BEEN CHOSEN

07:25.570 --> 07:27.029
AS THE IMPARTIAL
THIRD PARTY CARETAKER

07:27.113 --> 07:28.823
OF THIS MAGIC JELLY BEAN.

07:28.906 --> 07:29.448
GUARD IT WITH YOUR LIFE.

07:29.532 --> 07:31.367
- [barks inquisitively]

07:31.450 --> 07:32.368
- YES, THANK YOU, HAPPY.

07:32.451 --> 07:35.538
NEVER GIVE IT TO JUST ME
OR JUST HAPPY ALONE.

07:35.621 --> 07:38.040
WE'RE GONNA TAKE
A SMALL TIME-OUT,

07:38.124 --> 07:39.750
AND WE WILL COME BACK
TO YOU TOGETHER

07:39.834 --> 07:41.335
WHEN WE FIGURE OUT WHAT TO DO.

07:43.337 --> 07:45.548
- MR. PANTS
WILL TAKE THE DAY SHIFT.

07:45.631 --> 07:47.842
- [barks warningly]

07:47.925 --> 07:50.636
- I'M NOT GONNA EAT IT.

07:53.014 --> 07:56.851
- WELL, BYE, HAPS.

07:56.934 --> 07:59.562
I THINK I'M GONNA
GO GET AN APPRAISAL

07:59.645 --> 08:00.813
DOWN AT THE WIG SHOP.

08:00.897 --> 08:01.898
WHAT ARE YOU GONNA DO TODAY?

08:01.981 --> 08:03.065
[barks casually]

08:03.149 --> 08:05.318
- SOUNDS FUN.

08:05.401 --> 08:06.736
SEE YOU LATER, THEN.

08:06.819 --> 08:08.529
[footsteps]

08:10.072 --> 08:11.908
HAVE A GOOD DAY.

08:11.991 --> 08:14.243
- [barks slyly]

08:18.497 --> 08:20.249
- I'M GOIN' NOW, SO...

08:20.333 --> 08:22.752
- [barks slyly]

08:32.010 --> 08:32.970
[door creaks]

08:41.645 --> 08:43.563
[machinery whirring]

08:43.648 --> 08:46.275
thud!

08:46.359 --> 08:47.735
[grunts]

08:49.987 --> 08:51.155
[machinery whirring]

08:51.239 --> 08:54.742
[soft squeaking]

08:54.825 --> 08:56.702
[whimpers]

08:56.786 --> 08:59.247
gulp!

09:00.831 --> 09:03.125
[growls]

09:03.209 --> 09:06.420
- [chuffing drowsily]

09:09.423 --> 09:10.383
thwack!

09:10.466 --> 09:12.760
- NICE TRY,
ALLEGED BEST FRIEND.

09:12.843 --> 09:14.428
- [barking accusingly]

09:14.512 --> 09:15.388
- WHAT?

09:15.471 --> 09:17.348
THIS SKI MASK PROVES NOTHING.

09:17.431 --> 09:20.309
MY FACE WAS COLD.

09:22.562 --> 09:23.604
[birds chirping]

09:32.405 --> 09:34.991
- HAPPY, AFTER I GOT BACK

09:35.074 --> 09:37.118
FROM MY COMPLETELY
UNSUSPICIOUS WINDOW ACTIVITIES,

09:37.201 --> 09:39.495
I THOUGHT ABOUT IT,

09:39.578 --> 09:40.997
AND YOU SHOULD TAKE
THE JELLY BEAN.

09:41.080 --> 09:44.333
- [barks]
HUH?

09:44.417 --> 09:46.335
- NO, NO, NO, NO,
I MEAN IT; I MEAN IT.

09:46.419 --> 09:48.337
I WON'T BE ABLE
TO LIVE WITH THE GUILT

09:48.421 --> 09:52.300
OF KNOWING I DEPRIVED YOU
OF A NORMAL LIFE.

09:52.383 --> 09:56.220
- [barks suspiciously]

09:56.304 --> 09:57.430
- REVERSE PSYCHOLOGY?

09:57.513 --> 09:58.180
WHAT KIND OF WORLD
DO WE LIVE IN

09:58.264 --> 10:00.683
IF MY OWN BEST FRIEND

10:00.766 --> 10:03.185
REGARDS ME
WITH SUCH SKEPTICISM?

10:03.269 --> 10:05.896
OH, HAPPY,
YOU'VE REALLY HURT ME.

10:05.980 --> 10:07.565
YOU'VE CUT ME DEEP.

10:09.442 --> 10:11.402
- [barks grumblingly]

10:11.485 --> 10:13.654
- [gasps]
HAPPY, HOW COULD YOU?

10:13.738 --> 10:15.573
I THOUGHT YOU CARED ABOUT ME.

10:15.656 --> 10:16.532
- HUH?

10:16.615 --> 10:20.202
- OKAY, OKAY.
THIS HAS GONE FAR ENOUGH.

10:20.286 --> 10:22.538
HOW ABOUT THIS?

10:22.621 --> 10:23.122
BENJA--

10:23.205 --> 10:25.625
[rope groaning]

10:25.708 --> 10:26.709
[yelps]

10:26.792 --> 10:29.253
- HAIR NET!
[laughs]

10:29.337 --> 10:31.714
- BENJAMIN, AFTER MANY HOURS
OF CAREFUL CONSIDERATION,

10:31.797 --> 10:35.468
HAPPY AND I HAVE DECIDED TO DO
THE ADULT THING...

10:35.551 --> 10:37.261
AND FIGHT FOR IT!

10:49.523 --> 10:52.234
AHHHH...

10:52.318 --> 10:54.487
[eagle cries]

11:00.326 --> 11:02.912
[magical zapping]

11:02.995 --> 11:05.623
- [gasps]

11:05.706 --> 11:07.666
- AAAAH!

11:07.750 --> 11:08.668
crash!

11:12.505 --> 11:13.756
- IT WORKED.

11:13.839 --> 11:15.424
OH, HAPPY, I'M SO GLAD.

11:15.508 --> 11:18.135
BOY, WE REALLY LET THAT
SITUATION GET OUT OF HAND.

11:18.219 --> 11:19.428
- [barks affirmatively]

11:19.512 --> 11:22.390
- NO, NO, PLEASE.
IT WAS MY FAULT.

11:22.473 --> 11:25.101
EVEN THE MIGHTY SOMETIMES FALL.

11:25.184 --> 11:26.102
- [barks affirmatively]

11:26.185 --> 11:27.895
- YEAH,
WELL, YOU DID PUSH IT.

11:27.978 --> 11:30.606
- SHOULD WE TELL THEM,
MR. PANTS?

11:32.733 --> 11:35.444
YOU'RE RIGHT.
WHY RUIN THE MOMENT?

11:38.030 --> 11:38.447
- ♪ ONE, TWO ♪

11:38.531 --> 11:40.950
♪ BABY, GIRL ♪

11:41.033 --> 11:44.036
♪ COME CHECK OUT
MY NEW MERCHANDISE ♪

11:44.120 --> 11:44.995
♪ YEAH ♪

11:45.079 --> 11:46.080
- ♪ CHECK IT OUT,
CHECK IT OUT NOW, HUH! ♪

11:46.163 --> 11:48.749
- ♪ BABY, GIRL ♪

11:48.833 --> 11:52.670
♪ I KNOW YOU'RE GONNA
PAY THE PRICE ♪

11:52.753 --> 11:54.046
♪ YEAH ♪

11:54.130 --> 11:55.714
- ♪ IF YOU DON'T,
THEN YOUR MOM WILL, HUH! ♪

11:55.798 --> 11:57.299
- ♪ WHEN YOU WALK DOWN
THE STREET, GIRL ♪

11:57.383 --> 11:58.634
♪ YOU KNOW WHO WE ARE ♪

11:58.717 --> 12:01.721
♪ AND YOU FALL
AT MY FEET, GIRL ♪

12:01.804 --> 12:02.555
♪ 'CAUSE I'M A BIG STAR ♪

12:02.638 --> 12:05.808
♪ YOU GOT SO MUCH
TO SAY, GIRL ♪

12:05.891 --> 12:06.600
♪ BUT DON'T GO TOO FAR ♪

12:06.684 --> 12:09.478
♪ WANNA TAKE YOU AWAY, GIRL ♪

12:09.562 --> 12:11.272
♪ BUT I CAN'T DRIVE A CAR ♪

12:11.355 --> 12:12.565
♪ WE'RE THE BOYS ♪

12:12.648 --> 12:13.482
♪ WE'RE THE BOYS ♪

12:13.566 --> 12:15.943
♪ WE'RE THE SUGAR BOYS ♪

12:16.026 --> 12:19.447
♪ AND WE'LL ALWAYS LOVE YOU,
GIRL, I SWEAR ♪

12:19.530 --> 12:20.739
♪ WE'RE THE BOYS ♪

12:20.823 --> 12:21.657
♪ WE'RE THE BOYS ♪

12:21.740 --> 12:24.076
♪ WE'RE THE SUGAR BOYS ♪

12:24.160 --> 12:27.163
♪ JUST DON'T TOUCH US
OR YOU'LL MESS OUR HAIR ♪

12:27.246 --> 12:28.831
- HEY, ALL YOU SUGAR BOYS
SUPERFANS,

12:28.914 --> 12:30.833
THAT WAS EVERYONE'S
FAVORITE BOY BAND

12:30.916 --> 12:32.501
POWER-POPPIN' TO NUMBER ONE.

12:32.585 --> 12:33.502
NOW GET YOUR FINGERS
ON THE PULSE,

12:33.586 --> 12:36.005
OR AS I LIKE TO CALL IT,
THE DIAL,

12:36.088 --> 12:38.507
'CAUSE KRZY "CRAZY" FM

12:38.591 --> 12:40.468
IS ABOUT TO ROCK
OUR CALL-IN TRIVIA CONTEST

12:40.551 --> 12:42.470
FOR TWO--THAT'S RIGHT--
TWO TICKETS

12:42.553 --> 12:45.181
TO TONIGHT'S SOLD-OUT
SUGAR BOYS CONCERT.

12:45.264 --> 12:46.348
THAT'S RIGHT, KRZY-IES.

12:46.432 --> 12:48.559
YOU AND YOUR BESTEST BFF

12:48.642 --> 12:50.060
COULD POUR
SOME SUGAR ON YOURSELVES

12:50.144 --> 12:51.187
IN THREE, TWO, ONE...

12:51.270 --> 12:53.522
CRAZY DIAL.

12:53.606 --> 12:55.107
[phone keys beeping]

12:55.191 --> 12:56.650
- FASTER, FINGER, FASTER.

12:56.734 --> 12:58.194
- BOO-YAH!

12:58.277 --> 13:00.196
LOOKS LIKE WE GOT A CALL.

13:00.279 --> 13:01.739
HELLO? HELLO?
HELLO?

13:01.822 --> 13:03.157
callers: AWWW...

13:03.240 --> 13:04.575
- THIS IS BESSIE HIGGENBOTTOM,

13:04.658 --> 13:05.326
OCCASIONAL LISTENER,
AVID CALLER,

13:05.409 --> 13:07.661
AND I LOVE THE SUGAR BOYS!

13:07.745 --> 13:11.665
- WHOA-HO-HO,
SOMEONE'S CRAZY-EXCITED.

13:11.749 --> 13:13.459
- YOU BET
YOUR SWEET PATOOTIE I AM.

13:13.542 --> 13:15.002
WHAT'S THE QUESTION?

13:15.085 --> 13:16.545
DO I HAVE TO ANSWER THE QUESTION
IN THE FORM OF A QUESTION,

13:16.629 --> 13:17.379
OR SHOULD I ANSWER THE QUESTION
WITH AN ANSWER?

13:17.463 --> 13:18.547
HOW MUCH TIME DO I HAVE?

13:18.631 --> 13:19.548
IS THE QUESTION MULTIPLE CHOICE?

13:19.632 --> 13:20.966
CAN I HAVE THE COUNTRY OF ORIGIN

13:21.050 --> 13:23.093
FOR THE FIRST AND LAST WORD
OF THE QUESTION, PLEASE?

13:23.177 --> 13:24.803
- WHOA, WHOA, SLOW YOUR ROLL,
DADDY DANCER.

13:24.887 --> 13:26.889
NOW, HERE'S THE QUESTION.

13:26.972 --> 13:30.559
WHO WAS PRESIDENT TRUMAN'S
SECRETARY OF AGRICULTURE?

13:30.643 --> 13:33.562
- I'M NOT REALLY SURE
HOW TO ANSWER THAT...

13:33.646 --> 13:35.606
[callers sigh]

13:35.689 --> 13:38.567
BECAUSE TRUMAN HAD THREE
SECRETARIES OF AGRICULTURE

13:38.651 --> 13:39.401
DURING HIS TWO TERMS
AS PRESIDENT.

13:39.485 --> 13:40.819
DO YOU WANT ME TO LIST THEM

13:40.903 --> 13:43.405
IN CHRONOLOGICAL
OR ALPHABETICAL ORDER?

13:43.489 --> 13:47.284
- AND THAT IS A CORRECT ANSWER
TO A CRAZY TRICK QUESTION.

13:47.368 --> 13:48.702
ALL RIGHT!

13:48.786 --> 13:50.079
- YEAH!

13:50.162 --> 13:53.123
- BESSIE HIGGENBOTTOM,
YOU AND YOUR LUCKY PLUS ONE

13:53.207 --> 13:55.000
ARE GOIN' TO THE CONCERT!

13:55.084 --> 13:56.919
- WHOO!

13:57.002 --> 13:58.754
[screeching]

14:02.174 --> 14:03.884
- [gasps]

14:03.968 --> 14:06.762
- HERE, I BOUGHT THIS FOR YOU
ON DORK-DOT-GEEK.

14:06.845 --> 14:09.390
- A RETRACTABLE PROTRACTOR?

14:09.473 --> 14:11.725
I'VE ALWAYS WANTED A SPARE.

14:11.809 --> 14:13.102
HOW'D YOU KNOW?

14:13.185 --> 14:13.519
- A LITTLE NERD TOLD ME.

14:13.602 --> 14:15.396
- [growls]

14:15.479 --> 14:16.564
- SO LET'S CUT TO THE CHASE.

14:16.647 --> 14:17.773
MAKE ME PLUS ONE,

14:17.856 --> 14:19.692
I'LL GIVE YOU PROTECTION
FOR A YEAR.

14:19.775 --> 14:21.026
- WOW, I--

14:21.110 --> 14:22.736
- HEY, CONGRATS AND ALL THAT.

14:22.820 --> 14:24.154
SURE, I'LL BE YOUR PLUS ONE.
NO PROBS.

14:24.238 --> 14:25.322
- WELL, I--

14:25.406 --> 14:28.534
- HEY, BESSIE, IT'S ME,
YOUR BROTHER-BY-BLOOD, BEN.

14:28.617 --> 14:29.702
I CAN'T WAIT
FOR THE SUGAR BOYS.

14:29.785 --> 14:33.539
♪ WE'RE THE BOYS,
WE'RE THE SUGAR BOYS ♪

14:33.622 --> 14:35.374
- HEY, BUNGEE BOY.

14:35.457 --> 14:37.293
YOU SING THAT SONG
♪ UP HERE ♪

14:37.376 --> 14:40.170
IT'S A "C,"
NOT A "G," OKAY?

14:40.254 --> 14:42.172
COME ON, BESSIE,
LET'S MAKE IT OFFICIAL.

14:42.256 --> 14:44.300
TELL THE WORLD
I'M YOUR PLUS ONE.

14:44.383 --> 14:45.342
- DUDE, YOU'RE TRIPPIN'.

14:45.426 --> 14:47.469
- GUYS, GUYS,
YOU'RE ALL VERY SPECIAL TO ME.

14:47.553 --> 14:50.097
THIS DECISION REQUIRES

14:50.180 --> 14:51.974
CAREFUL CONSIDERATION
OF ALL APPLICANTS

14:52.057 --> 14:54.977
AS WELL AS A PRUDENT REVIEW
OF RELEVANT FACTORS

14:55.060 --> 14:59.315
AND UNFORESEEN VARIABLES.

14:59.398 --> 15:00.566
[door slams]

15:00.649 --> 15:02.151
- [barking argumentatively]

15:02.234 --> 15:04.153
- WHAT DO YOU MEAN,
<i>YOUR</i> TICKET?

15:04.236 --> 15:05.821
YOU DON'T EVEN
LIKE THE SUGAR BOYS.

15:05.904 --> 15:07.406
YOU MAKE FUN OF THEM
ALL THE TIME.

15:07.489 --> 15:10.909
LOOK WHAT YOU DID TO TATE.

15:10.993 --> 15:15.205
- [barking a melody]

15:15.289 --> 15:17.166
- OH, PLEASE.
YOU DON'T EVEN KNOW THE WORDS.

15:17.249 --> 15:19.793
MY PLUS ONE TICKET DESERVES
TO GO TO SOMEONE

15:19.877 --> 15:21.420
WHO TRULY LOVES AND RESPECTS
THE SUGAR BOYS.

15:21.503 --> 15:24.048
- [growls]

15:29.261 --> 15:29.970
- [sniffs]

15:30.054 --> 15:32.931
AH, LOVE THAT NEW TICKET SMELL.

15:33.015 --> 15:34.308
- YO, BESSIE!

15:34.391 --> 15:34.975
- OH.

15:35.059 --> 15:36.935
- BESSIE!
- HEY, BESSIE!

15:39.521 --> 15:41.357
- HERE.
I'M A SEMI-NATURAL BLONDE.

15:41.440 --> 15:43.859
- OH, UM...

15:43.942 --> 15:47.112
- EW, WHY WOULD
ANYONE WANT THAT?

15:47.196 --> 15:48.697
- UH, BECAUSE IT'S MINE.

15:48.781 --> 15:50.699
- YEAH, YOUR SPLIT ENDS.

15:50.783 --> 15:54.119
- [gasps]
MY ENDS DO NOT SPLIT.

15:54.203 --> 15:56.288
TAKE IT BACK!

15:56.372 --> 15:58.457
- IT'S FINE.
I LOVE HAIR.

15:58.540 --> 15:59.541
THANK YOU.
WHAT A WONDERFUL PRESENT.

15:59.625 --> 16:00.959
- YOU'RE JEALOUS,
AND YOU ALWAYS DISS ME, AND...

16:01.043 --> 16:03.212
[phone rings]
- OOH, GOTTA TAKE THIS.

16:03.295 --> 16:06.882
AMBASSADOR, HOW ARE YOU?

16:06.965 --> 16:08.217
OH, HOLD ON A SECOND.

16:08.300 --> 16:10.969
THIS IS BESSIE.
HI, MILLIE.

16:11.053 --> 16:13.222
I'D LOVE TO GO
TO BINGO WITH YOU.

16:13.305 --> 16:15.057
YEAH--WAIT, WAIT.
I HAVE ANOTHER CALL.

16:15.140 --> 16:16.225
BESSIE HERE.

16:16.308 --> 16:17.518
OH, HELLO, DOCTOR.

16:17.601 --> 16:19.228
I THOUGHT MY
NEXT SCHEDULED CLEANING SESSION

16:19.311 --> 16:20.771
WAS IN 121 DAYS.

16:20.854 --> 16:23.440
OH, YOU JUST CALLED TO TALK?

16:23.524 --> 16:25.401
OOPS.
WAIT, I HAVE ANOTHER CALL.

16:25.484 --> 16:26.402
I'M GETTING PRETTY BUSY
SMACKING MY GUMS TODAY.

16:26.485 --> 16:28.404
GET IT?

16:28.487 --> 16:29.029
OKAY, GOTTA SWITCH.

16:29.113 --> 16:31.323
I CAN'T TALK NOW, HAPS.

16:31.407 --> 16:33.242
EVERYONE WANTS TO BE MY BFF.

16:33.325 --> 16:34.410
THIS IS B-DAWG.
TALK TO ME.

16:34.493 --> 16:37.162
- [growls]

16:37.246 --> 16:39.456
- ♪ WE'RE THE BOYS,
WE'RE THE BOYS ♪

16:39.540 --> 16:42.418
♪ WE'RE THE SUGAR BOYS ♪

16:42.501 --> 16:44.878
- WHEW.
HUNGRY.

16:44.962 --> 16:47.131
I NEED TO REFUEL MY COOL TANK.

16:47.214 --> 16:50.259
- GREAT CHOICE.
THIS ONE'S ON ME.

16:50.342 --> 16:52.261
THANKS.
MMM.

16:52.344 --> 16:54.972
- IF YOU TAKE ME
AS YOUR PLUS ONE,

16:55.055 --> 16:56.807
YOU CAN RIDE WITH ME
IN THE MINIVAN

16:56.890 --> 16:58.392
IN THE FRONT
BOTH WAYS.

16:58.475 --> 17:00.352
- MOMMY!

17:00.436 --> 17:01.270
SORRY, PORTIA.

17:01.353 --> 17:04.314
ALL'S FAIR IN LOVE
AND THE SUGAR BOYS.

17:04.397 --> 17:05.773
♪ WE'RE THE BOYS,
WE'RE THE BOYS ♪

17:05.858 --> 17:07.984
♪ WE'RE THE SUGAR BOYS ♪

17:08.068 --> 17:08.484
splat!

17:08.569 --> 17:12.406
- WANT A RIDE, B?

17:12.489 --> 17:15.492
- WHEEEEE!

17:15.576 --> 17:17.453
- [growling]

17:17.536 --> 17:19.204
- AND, BESSIE, SERIOUSLY,
IF YOU TAKE ME,

17:19.288 --> 17:21.290
I'LL LAUGH AT YOUR JOKES
FOR A WHOLE YEAR.

17:21.373 --> 17:22.540
- HI. BESSIE.

17:22.624 --> 17:25.502
CHESTER TURTLETON
WROTE A HAIKU FOR YOU.

17:25.586 --> 17:27.671
- REALLY? I'M SO FLATTERED.

17:29.840 --> 17:31.383
- GO ON, CHESTER.

17:31.467 --> 17:32.426
GO ON.

17:32.509 --> 17:32.926
GO ON!

17:33.010 --> 17:34.386
- TURTLE HAIKU?

17:34.470 --> 17:35.971
ARE YOU KIDDING?

17:36.054 --> 17:37.598
LIKE BESSIE
UNDERSTANDS JAPANESE.

17:37.681 --> 17:38.557
- I AGREE.

17:38.640 --> 17:41.310
TOTALLY WEAK.

17:41.393 --> 17:42.895
YOU KNOW WHAT'S NOT WEAK?

17:42.978 --> 17:43.187
A PANDA.

17:45.397 --> 17:47.232
THAT'S NOT A PANDA.

17:47.316 --> 17:49.985
THAT'S A BABY PANDA.

17:50.068 --> 17:51.445
[inhales sharply]

17:53.655 --> 17:55.032
PANDA...
PANDA, PANDA, PANDA.

17:55.115 --> 17:57.534
PANDA, PANDA,
PANDA, PANDA, PANDA.

17:57.618 --> 17:59.536
- [shrieks]

17:59.620 --> 18:02.581
[both screaming]

18:02.664 --> 18:04.458
[cat snarling]

18:08.253 --> 18:10.422
- [groans]

18:10.506 --> 18:14.051
[grunting]

18:14.134 --> 18:15.844
OH, HELLO, MR. PRESIDENT.

18:15.928 --> 18:19.097
<i>NOW</i> HE'S RETURNING MY CALLS.

18:19.181 --> 18:21.725
YES, I DID HEAR
FROM YOUR PEOPLE.

18:21.809 --> 18:23.894
I AM VERY AWARE
OF YOUR INTEREST.

18:23.977 --> 18:27.356
- [barks angrily]

18:27.439 --> 18:29.441
- I'M SORRY, SIR.
CAN I CALL YOU BACK?

18:29.525 --> 18:31.902
HAPPY, I HOPE
YOU HAVE A GOOD REASON

18:31.985 --> 18:32.653
FOR INTERRUPTING
FEDERAL BUSINESS.

18:32.736 --> 18:35.948
- [barking]

18:36.031 --> 18:38.575
{\an5}- [sighs]
LOOK, IF YOU REALLY WANT
TO PITCH YOURSELF

18:38.659 --> 18:39.910
AS MY PLUS ONE,

18:39.993 --> 18:42.162
I WILL TRY TO SQUEEZE YOU IN

18:42.246 --> 18:44.706
AFTER MY 4:30 SHIRLEY Ts
WITH ANTON.

18:44.790 --> 18:47.376
THAT'S OUR NICKNAME
FOR SHIRLEY TEMPLES.

18:47.459 --> 18:50.170
[banging at door]

18:51.046 --> 18:52.714
- UM, THIS USED
TO BELONG TO GWEN,

18:52.798 --> 18:54.883
BUT IT'S YOURS NOW.

18:56.218 --> 18:58.387
- AHHH...

18:58.470 --> 19:02.850
DOES THIS MEAN
WHAT MY HEART WANTS IT TO MEAN?

19:02.933 --> 19:05.477
REAL, TRUE BFFs?

19:05.561 --> 19:08.397
- YEAH, AND YOUR
REAL, TRUE PLUS ONE?

19:08.480 --> 19:10.232
- OH. YEAH.

19:10.315 --> 19:12.609
I MEAN, WE ARE CONNECTED.

19:12.693 --> 19:13.610
- YES!

19:13.694 --> 19:14.987
TICKET.
GIVE ME.

19:16.572 --> 19:19.324
- [gasps]

19:22.786 --> 19:25.372
UM, YOU KNOW, TICKETS
LIKE TO STICK TOGETHER,

19:25.455 --> 19:26.623
JUST LIKE BFFs.

19:26.707 --> 19:27.875
UM, I'LL GIVE 'EM TO YOU
AT THE SHOW.

19:27.958 --> 19:30.919
- [sighs]
I'M GONNA GO GET READY.

19:31.003 --> 19:32.921
I'LL CALL YOU
IN A LITTLE WHILE

19:33.005 --> 19:34.423
WITH INSTRUCTIONS
ON WHAT TO WEAR.

19:34.506 --> 19:36.341
- SURE. YEAH.

19:36.425 --> 19:36.758
DON'T WANNA CLASH.

19:36.842 --> 19:38.427
[door shuts]

19:38.510 --> 19:40.345
THE SHOW'S IN AN HOUR!

19:40.429 --> 19:41.722
I HAVE TO FIND THE TICKETS.

19:41.805 --> 19:44.099
NOT HERE.
NOPE.

19:44.182 --> 19:46.476
FIND TICKETS.
NO.

19:46.560 --> 19:48.854
- THE CONCERT'S IN AN HOUR.

19:48.937 --> 19:50.314
WHAT AM I GONNA DO, HAPPY?

19:50.397 --> 19:53.066
[sobbing]

19:53.150 --> 19:57.613
WHAT AM I GOING TO DO?

19:57.696 --> 20:00.282
- [barks explanatorily]

20:00.365 --> 20:04.286
- GO TO THE BOX OFFICE
AND BEG FOR REPLACEMENT TICKETS?

20:04.369 --> 20:06.997
YES!

20:08.874 --> 20:11.168
HI, THERE.
NICE VEST.

20:11.251 --> 20:11.793
LISTEN, I'M SURE
IT'S NO BIG THING,

20:11.877 --> 20:14.004
BUT I LOST MY TICKETS,

20:14.087 --> 20:14.838
AND I WANTED TO PICK UP
A REPLACEMENT PAIR.

20:14.922 --> 20:17.758
- [laughs hysterically]

20:17.841 --> 20:19.509
- PSST!
[whistles]

20:19.593 --> 20:23.096
PSST.

20:25.724 --> 20:29.269
- UGH, WHAT DO YOU THINK I AM,
A BAJILLIONAIRE?

20:29.353 --> 20:30.687
IF I HAD THAT KIND OF MONEY,

20:30.771 --> 20:31.647
I WOULDN'T BE SHOPPING
AT A CARDBOARD BOX.

20:31.730 --> 20:34.149
- [barks helpfully]

20:34.232 --> 20:36.860
- YOU ALSO TAKE
DOG BISCUITS?

20:36.944 --> 20:38.153
- [barks affirmatively]

20:38.236 --> 20:40.906
- FINE, A BAKER'S DOZEN.
SHOW ME THE TICKETS.

20:45.243 --> 20:51.500
AJXTQUTT275891 4/8ths
XRZ51MX2A975T?

20:51.583 --> 20:53.210
THESE ARE MY TICKETS!

20:58.131 --> 20:59.216
HAPPY?

20:59.299 --> 21:01.051
HOW COULD YOU?

21:01.134 --> 21:01.843
WHY WOULD YOU?

21:01.927 --> 21:04.262
WAIT, I THINK I KNOW.

21:04.346 --> 21:05.389
thud!

21:05.472 --> 21:08.016
THIS IS OBVIOUSLY
A CRY FOR HELP.

21:08.100 --> 21:10.686
OH, WHY DIDN'T I
SEE THIS BEFORE?

21:10.769 --> 21:13.855
IT'S THAT CONCERT
THAT DID THIS TO US.

21:13.939 --> 21:15.524
WHAT'S A SUGAR BOYS SHOW

21:15.607 --> 21:17.776
{\an5}COMPARED TO THE BEAUTIFUL MUSIC
OF OUR FRIENDSHIP?

21:17.859 --> 21:19.361
IF IT'S GONNA TEAR US APART,

21:19.444 --> 21:20.529
I DON'T WANT TO GO.

21:20.612 --> 21:22.197
- SAY WHAT-WHAT?

21:22.280 --> 21:25.033
- PORTIA, I KNOW YOU'VE BEEN
COUNTING ON GOING WITH ME,

21:25.117 --> 21:26.076
BUT YOU HAVE TO TAKE
BOTH OF MY TICKETS.

21:26.159 --> 21:28.745
NOW, DON'T TRY
TO TALK ME OUT OF--

21:28.829 --> 21:29.621
- GWEN!
TIX.

21:29.705 --> 21:31.707
- TOTES.

21:34.126 --> 21:35.335
- I JUST WANT

21:35.419 --> 21:36.712
TO SPEND SOME QUALITY TIME
WITH YOU, HAPS.

21:36.795 --> 21:39.131
- [whimpers]

21:39.214 --> 21:41.800
[smooches]

21:41.883 --> 21:44.344
- TONIGHT YOU GET PEOPLE FOOD.

21:44.428 --> 21:48.223
TOFU PARMESAN
WITH SOY-TATOES.

21:48.307 --> 21:49.516
- [grumbles]

21:49.599 --> 21:52.144
- [audience cheering]

21:52.227 --> 21:53.437
- YEAH.

21:53.520 --> 21:54.771
- I LOVE YOUR HIGHLIGHTS.

21:54.855 --> 21:57.858
- ♪ WE'RE THE BOYS ♪

21:57.941 --> 21:59.067
♪ WE'RE THE BOYS ♪

21:59.151 --> 22:00.777
